I just started a new job and was browsing through confluence. As I looked through the table of contents for useful information and reviewed interesting documents, I found myself looking at the last updated date a lot and skipping over stuff that was years old.

I'd be interested in some kind of plugin that showed how fresh each leaf document is by looking at its node in the left hand TOC. I see ranging continuously from green (updated in the last month) through yellow (updated in the last six months) to red (updated more than a year ago).

It may also be useful to roll up the colors of each individual page to the higher levels of the TOC. For example, you have three top level TOC entries, and underneath each top level entry there are three documents. In the first top level, the documents are all older than one year, so the top level is red. In the second there is one document older than a year, but the other two were updated last week, so the top level is greenish-yellow. In the third, all three documents were updated today, so the top level is green.

