I'm trying to create a decision in a decision log in one of our sites and I'm not able to create one. When I click the macro to create a decision from the decision template, I get no visible response. I do however see that I'm getting an HTTP 400 response from the AJAX call that it's trying to make. My response is as follows:

{code}
{"errorCode":400,"errorType":"NOT_FOUND:SPACE","errorData":"10536","errorMessage":"No space found for spaceKey '10536'"}
{code}

When I start editing the macro which is supposed to create a template I notice that it does not specify a space key, it's left blank, which according to the description right below the parameter field should mean it's using the space that the decision log lives in. What's interesting is that when I try to specify a space key while editing the macro, it will autocomplete for me to "*0*10536" not "10536". However, even if I save the space key parameter for this macro to be "010536" it still gives me the error above. On top of all that, this works just fine for other spaces (i.e. one that has a space key of "10536WG"). From my very limited standpoint, it would appear there is a bug with this macro related to numerical space keys that start with a leading zero.

Let me know if I can provide more detail in any way. Thanks.

Oh, yeah, and a shout out to Issac. Idk why, just because I can I suppose.

